create

public DataType create(DataType toCreate)
To put object in graph, we have to find all its fields, then put them in graph elements. Notice this method directly calls doUpdate(Object, CascadeType, Map), just checking before that if an id must be generated. If an id must be generated, then it is (and so is associated vertex, to make sure no problem will arise later).

create in interface AbstractCrudService<DataType>

getVertexFor

public com.tinkerpop.blueprints.pgm.Vertex getVertexFor(Object value,
                                                        javax.persistence.CascadeType cascade,
                                                        Map<String,Object> objectsBeingUpdated)
Get vertex associated to value. If object is managed by a service, we ask this service the value

Parameters:
value - value we want the vertex for
cascade - used cascade type, can be either CascadeType.PERSIST or CascadeType.MERGE
objectsBeingUpdated - map of objects currently being updated, it avoid some loops during update, but is absolutely NOT a persistent cache
Returns:
vertex for given value. May be null in some rare cases (typically obtaining a vertex that doesn't exist yet for deleting it)
